# Guidelines on adding links

Links MUST go to user-visible pages (not raw HTTP APIs unless there's no better option and users can open them to see data).

## CRITICAL: Links MUST be relevant and properly scoped

Links MUST match BOTH:
1. **Investigation topic**: Network issues → network dashboards, CPU issues → CPU dashboards, NOT mismatched topics
2. **Issue level**: Pod issues → pod-level dashboards, namespace issues → namespace-level, NOT wrong scope

## CRITICAL: Links MUST include all relevant query parameters

Include ALL relevant query parameters (namespace, pod, service, cluster, time range, etc.) in the URL. For Grafana, include all variables (var-namespace, var-pod, etc.). DO NOT generate links without parameters and tell users to "filter by X".

**CORRECT:** `http://grafana_url.com/d/abc123/pod-network?orgId=1&var-namespace=app-163&var-pod=payment-service-abc123`

**INCORRECT:** 
- `http://grafana_url.com/d/abc123/namespace-overview?orgId=1&var-namespace=app-163` (wrong scope)
- `http://grafana_url.com/d/abc123/pod-cpu?orgId=1&var-namespace=app-163&var-pod=payment-service-abc123` (wrong topic for network investigation)
- `http://grafana_url.com/d/ff635a025bcfea7bc3dd4f508990a3e9/kubernetes-networking-cluster` (out of scope when a more scoped relevant dashboard exists like pod or namespace)
